<!-- see 'textless events' in modding tips folder -->
<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_COMBAT_OFFENSE_DISABLER">
    <title>Offense Disabler</title>
    <desc>(RK Punk gear) This combat augment can fully disable enemy offense for 5 seconds. The effect becomes weaker until it's gone at 18 seconds (you will be warned). Affected systems:
		-Weapons
		-Drone Control
		-Hacking
		-Mind Control
		-Teleporter
		-all Artilleries
		Perfect against aggressive enemies! [Uses 2| and 3 reactor power. Emergency Generator can apply.]</desc>
    <cost>70</cost>
    <rarity>4</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<!-- [OUTDATED, Rework below.]
Jump event augment! Code is still in combat augment xml for technical reasons though.
Disabled because too damn CLUNKY since it forces player to confirm every jump, even without having the augment...
Some add-on that came out in the meantime has done a better implementation of this, check it out.

<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_JUMP_DECOY">
    <title>Jump Decoy</title>
    <desc>When you escape a fight by performing an FTL jump, this sends a fake jump signature to a different destination. Your enemy has a 25% chance to transmit this misleading intel, delaying the rebel fleet for 1 turn.</desc>
    <cost>30</cost>
    <rarity>1</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

REWORKED JumpDecoy -->
<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_HACK_FLEET">
    <title>Enigmashin</title>
    <desc>(RK Punk gear) This combat augment attempts to send deepfake intel to the rebels through an enemy's comms for credibility. Success delays the fleet, Crit-fail accelerates it.
		If you deal more than 2 hull damage during the process, it stops. 
		
		Free use takes 17 seconds. Limit your Hacking system and use droneparts for faster, better results. (Someone might notice)
		
		Chances (Good / Crit / Crit-fail)
		0| no hacking = 60% / 5% / 15%
		1| hacking 1 = 70% / 10% / 10%
		2| hacking 2 = 80% / 15% / 5% / +???
		3| hacking 3 = 90% / 20% / 5% / +???
		</desc>
    <cost>35</cost>
    <rarity>3</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_SUPER_DEFENDERS">
    <title>Defense Kits</title>
    <desc>(RK Punk gear) Makes your crew better at survival on your ship.
	x0.75 damage taken, x1.3 repair speed, x1.3 movement speed, and a 4 HP/second heal while idle (not even manning).</desc>
    <cost>90</cost>
    <rarity>4</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<!-- Daft Punk H B F S reference -->
<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_OWN_HARMONY_ON">
    <title>Punk Harmony</title>
    <desc>Some daft RadiKal Punks made their own Harmony. Controls your Engis on your ship, giving them immunity to (further) mind control and +40% resistance to damage and stun. Powered levels in Hacking or Mind Control add 5/10/20/40/80/160% combat damage, and repair and movement speed.
	
	In short, makes them harder, better, faster, stronger, and automated.
	
	Can be toggled off anytime.</desc>
    <cost>55</cost>
    <rarity>5</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>
<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_OWN_HARMONY_OFF">
    <title>Punk Harmony (OFF)</title>
    <desc>Some daft RadiKal Punks made their own Harmony. Controls your Engis on your ship, giving them immunity to (further) mind control and +40% resistance to damage and stun. Powered levels in Hacking or Mind Control add 5/10/20/40/80/160% combat damage, and repair and movement speed.
	
	In short, makes them harder, better, faster, stronger, and automated.
	
	Can be toggled on anytime.</desc>
    <cost>55</cost>
    <rarity>0</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_DEFENSE_REMOVER">
    <title>Vulnerabilizer</title>
    <desc>(RK Punk gear) This combat augment slowly weakens the enemy's defenses. Every 3 to 7 seconds (at random), limits enemy Shields and Engines by 1 power. This effect stacks. All effects end after 20 to 40 seconds. [Uses 2-4 | and 3 reactor power. Emergency Generator can apply.]</desc>
    <cost>80</cost>
    <rarity>5</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>
</FTL>

