////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//////////////////////////////////////////////////////TOOLBOX
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
See weapon tuto part 1 https://docs.google.com/document/d/1DNlSWG0l_FdxNo2QxlI5c-_dvlXp_3zxvsza78o2B78/edit 
and part 2 https://docs.google.com/document/d/1zDyIQ4xBYtBMyCD3671D1oTzAy_f9uIZg-9IbVwP5uc/edit
and part 3 https://docs.google.com/document/d/1uFne5fVc3B01ONuLOoa1IcmulctPmjazsqR1ovz-T18/edit
for more.

************************************************************************************************************************
				WEAPONS
************************************************************************************************************************

<weaponBlueprint name="(WRITE THE NAME OF THE WEAPON HERE)"> 

<type>WEAPON TYPE HERE! Such as "BURST" "LASER" "MISSILE" "BEAM" etc</type>
<title>What is the weapon's name?</title>
<short>What is the weapon's shortened name?</short>
<desc>What will the player read for the weapon's flavor text?</desc>
<tooltip>	An optional tooltip for the weapon if the player should be given advise on its purpose or usage(I believe this line is defunct, the tooltip is now called from the <tip> tag,
			which I will not teach today to keep things simple, as tooltips are optional!</tooltip>

<damage>How much hull damage does it do? Must be a number, no letters</damage>
<shots>How many times does it fire, per charge?</shots>

<fireTime>0.0</fireTime>       OVERRIDES THE FIRING ANIMATION SPEED and replaces it with the value you declare. Default is 1.0 for bombs and charge weapons, and 0.25 for other weapons. 
							Does not apply to beams.The lower the number, the FASTER the weapon fires. Can even go to low decimals, like 0.05. The higher the number, the slower it fires


<sp>Shield piercing: How many layers of the enemy ship's shield does the weapon pierce through?</sp>

<fireChance>Chance of weapon starting a fire. Every number stands for 10%, up to 100%. 
So if you set this to "5" then the weapon has a 50% chance to create a fire</fireChance>
<breachChance>Same as fire chance, chance to create a hull breach</breachChance>		BASED ON CHANCE TO NOT CAUSE FIRE!

<cooldown>How many seconds until the weapon can fully charge and fire? must be a number, no letters</cooldown>
<power>The amount of power needed to power and use the weapon</power>

<cost>How much scrap does it cost? Note: half of this number is the sell price</cost>
<bp>I believe this is the blueprint group. An unused tag. I just include it to be safe but it does nothing at all.</bp>
<rarity>How often will it appear in stores or events? "0" makes it never appear except for specific conditions you would have to code separately. </rarity>

<image>Declares the weapon's projectile in animations.xml. You could even do silly things like make a laser shoot missiles instead of lasers.</image>

<projectiles> and <image> are mutually exclusive. If you declare one, DO NOT ! ! ! ! ! ! ! ! declare the other, or they will interfere with each other and either break the weapon or crash the game.

<launchSounds>What sound effects does the game play when this weapon is fired? Can customize, but leave it default for now</launchSounds>
<hitShipSounds>What sound effects does the game play when this weapon's projectile hits a ship? Can customize, but leave it default for now</hitShipSounds>
<hitShieldSounds>What sound effects does the game play when this weapon's projectile hits a shield? Can customize, but leave it default for now</hitShieldSounds>
<missSounds>What sound effects does the game play when this weapon's projectile misses a ship? Can customize, but leave it default for now</missSounds>

<weaponArt>This line declares what animation sheet the weapon will use (and then the animation sheet declares which sprite sheet). WILL BE COVERED in another guide, leave it default</weaponArt>
<iconImage>I believe this calls the "icon" image to the left of each weapon's name in your weapon bar in-game. Leave it default for now</iconImage>

</weaponBlueprint> This line is the end of the weapon's code. Make sure every new weapon you make STARTS with "<weaponBlueprint>" and ENDS with "</weaponBlueprint>"


